{"lemma":"خُدْعاتٌ","slug":"خُدْعاتٌ","root":"خ.د.ع","root_slug":"خ-د-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-د-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10117","n10118","n10127","n10128","n10129","n10130"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%92%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"trick, deception","examples":[{"text":"هُوَ مُتَوَتِّرٌ وَلٰكِنَّهُ مُتَحَمِّسٌ لِتَقْدِيمِ خُدَعِهِ السِّحْرِيَّةِ فِي حَفْلَةِ عِيدِ الْمِيلَادِ.","english":"He's nervous but eager to debut his magic tricks at the birthday party."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/xud.ʕa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10117","headword_ar":"خَدَعَهُ","root":"xdE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEN","text_ar":"خَدْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Bd in ii. 8,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hid it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"concealed it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxdEh","text_ar":"اخدعه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ixodaAEN","text_ar":"اـِخْدَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":709},{"kind":"text","text":"[And hence, app.,] (Lh, K,) inf. n. as above, (Lh,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He doubled it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"folded it, one part upon another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a garment, or piece of cloth. (Lh, K, TA.) ―         -b3-  [And hence, also, accord. to some,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEahu","text_ar":"خَدَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEN","text_ar":"خَدْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidoEN","text_ar":"خِدْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, S, K,) or the latter is a simple subst., (Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadiyEapN","text_ar":"خَدِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or this [also] is a simple subst., (Msb, TA,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidaAEN","text_ar":"خِدَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is also an inf. n. of 3,] and like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xudNEapN","text_ar":"خُدٌعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He deceived, deluded, beguiled, circumvented,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outwitted, him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xatalahu","text_ar":"خَتَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desired to do to him a foul, an abominable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an evil, action, without his knowing whence it proceeded:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he dissembled"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acted deceitfully"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with him; pretended to him the contrary of what he concealed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made him to resign,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relinquish, the object that he had in view, by pretending to him something the contrary of what he concealed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, B:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xAdEhu","text_ar":"خادعهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxaAdaEapN","text_ar":"مُخَادَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidaAEN","text_ar":"خِدَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], signifies the same; (S, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxtdEhu","text_ar":"اختدعهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"txd~Ehu","text_ar":"تخدّعهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xd~Ehu","text_ar":"خدّعهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taxodiyEN","text_ar":"تَخْدِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or this last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he deceived him, deluded him, beguiled him, circumvented him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outwitted him, much:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL:) [and of another of these verbs we find the following various explanations:] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xAdEhu","text_ar":"خادعهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAyadahu","text_ar":"كَايَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which has the first of the meanings assigned in this sentence to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEahu","text_ar":"خَدَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he practised with him mutual deceit, delusion, guile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumvention; he deceived him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being deceived,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and this latter meaning, if not each meaning, may be intended here by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kAydh","text_ar":"كايده"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for Bd says, (in ii. 8,) that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxaAdaEap","text_ar":"مُخَادَعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is between two]: (TA:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he strove, endeavoured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desired, to deceive, delude, beguile, circumvent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outwit, him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AAF, L;) [agreeably with what is said by Kemál Páshá Zádeh, (as I find in a marginal note in a copy of the MS, and also in the Kull p. 178,) that one says of a man"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xAdE","text_ar":"خادع"},{"kind":"text","text":"when he has not attained his desire, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEa","text_ar":"خَدَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when he has attained his desire;] for many a verb of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEala","text_ar":"فَاعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"relates to one only; as in the instances of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAqabotu All~iS~a","text_ar":"عَاقَبْتُ اللِّصَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAraqotu","text_ar":"طَارَقْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aEola","text_ar":"النَّعْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) or it signifies, [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEahu","text_ar":"خَدَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he pretended to him something different from that which was in his mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) It is said in the Kur [ii. 8],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`ha waA@l~a*iyna A=manuwA","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهَ وَا@لَّذِينَ ا=مَنُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuxaAdiEuwna","text_ar":"يُخَادِعُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They pretend, to God and to those who have believed, something different from that which is in their minds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by concealing unbelief and pretending belief; for when they do thus to the believers, they do thus to God: (K:) and again, [in iv. 141],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`ha wahuwa xaAdiEuhumo","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهَ وَهُوَ خَادِعُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuxaAdiEuwna","text_ar":"يُخَادِعُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They strive, endeavour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desire, to deceive God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they think that they deceive God, but He is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their deceiver,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the requiter, to them, of their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidaAE","text_ar":"خِدَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (TA:) or the meaning is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they deceive"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the friends of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and [agreeably with this last rendering, and that given in the K,] Aboo-Hayáh reads, in the former passage,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxodaEuwna A@ll~`ha","text_ar":"يَخْدَعُونَ ا@للّٰهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [which passage continues thus:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA A^anofusahumo","text_ar":"اـِلَّا اَنْفُسَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaA yuxaAdiEuwna","text_ar":"وَمَا يُخَادِعُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but they do not deceive any save themselves"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the re-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sult of their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidaAE","text_ar":"خِدَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"does not befall any save themselves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) here, again, Aboo-Hayáh reads"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxodaEuwna","text_ar":"يَخْدَعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) Muärrik reads"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamaA","text_ar":"وَمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxad~iEuwna","text_ar":"يَخَدِّعُونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxotadiEuwna","text_ar":"يَخْتَدِعُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) Accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxadoEu","text_ar":"الخَدْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manoEu AlHaq~i","text_ar":"مَنْعُ الحَقِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The preventing from discovering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accepting, the truth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.) [“ He deceived him, ” or the like, seems to be generally regarded as the primary signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEahu","text_ar":"خَدَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for it occupies the first place in all the lexicons to which I have access: but Bd says (in ii. 8) that this meaning is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEa","text_ar":"خَدَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~i","text_ar":"ضَبِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that the primary signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEN","text_ar":"خَدْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the act of “ concealing: ” the action of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", however, as will appear in what follows, implies, and originates from, a desire of deceit; and so, often, does the act of concealing.] ―         -b4-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEotuhu","text_ar":"خَدَعْتُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gained the mastery over him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEa","text_ar":"خَدَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, TA, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEN","text_ar":"خَدْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) said of a [lizard of the kind called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dab~","text_ar":"ضَبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as though meaning either"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEa AlmuHotari$a","text_ar":"خَدَعَ المُحْتَرِشَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It deceived the hunter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEa nafosahu","text_ar":"خَدَعَ نَفْسَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it concealed itself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it entered into its hole;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEa fiY Hujorihi","text_ar":"خَدَعَ فِى حُجْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it scented a man, and therefore entered its hole, in order that it might not be caught;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnxdE","text_ar":"انخدع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it entered into its hole in a tortuous manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner, a gazelle"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into its covert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but mostly said of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Abu-l-'Omeythil:) also said of other things: (Lth:) of a fox, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took to going to the right and left, deceitfully,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guilefully:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of a man, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he hid himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"from another: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he assumed a disposition not his own."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidaAEN","text_ar":"خِدَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] ―         -b6-  Hence, i. e. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEa","text_ar":"خَدَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Db~","text_ar":"ضبّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEato Eayonu Al$~amosi","text_ar":"خَدَعَتْ عَيْنُ الشَّمْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The disc of the sun set;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaDaEato","text_ar":"خَضَعَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xDE","text_ar":"خضع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b7-  [And]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEato Eayonuhu","text_ar":"خَدَعَتْ عَيْنُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His eye sank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became depressed, in his head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K, TA.) [Also meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His eye did not sleep:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEati","text_ar":"خَدَعَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEayonu","text_ar":"العَيْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the eye did not sleep."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b8-  [Hence also, as indicated in the S,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA xadaEato","text_ar":"مَا خَدَعَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY EayoniY naEosapN","text_ar":"فِى عَيْنِى نَعْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slumber did not enter my eye"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA xadaEato biEayonihi naEosapN","text_ar":"مَا خَدَعَتْ بِعَيْنِهِ نَعْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the L,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEapN","text_ar":"خَدْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEosapN","text_ar":"نَعْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the TA,) meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a slumber did not pass by his eye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) [And from the same source have originated several other tropical significations, of which exs. here follow.] ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEati AlA^umuwri","text_ar":"خَدَعَتِ الاُمُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The affairs varied in their state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"were,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, variable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, K.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEati Als~uwqu","text_ar":"خَدَعَتِ السُّوقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEN","text_ar":"خَدْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The market varied in its state; at one time being brisk, and at another time dull, in respect of traffic:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAdiEN","text_ar":"خَادِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below:) or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the market became dull in respect of traffic;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnxdEt","text_ar":"انخدعت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, TA;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnxdE","text_ar":"انخدع"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K: [but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swq","text_ar":"سوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is generally fem.:]) and, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became brisk in respect of traffic:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus it appears to have two contr. significations: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEa Als~iEoru","text_ar":"خَدَعَ السِّعْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The price became high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b11-  Said of a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEa","text_ar":"خَدَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His wealth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became small in amount,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"little."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b12-  Said of a time, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEN","text_ar":"خَدْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Its rain became little:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and of rain, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became little."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b13-  Said of spittle, or saliva, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It dried:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became little, and dried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the mouth: (A, TA.) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became deficient;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and when it becomes deficient, it becomes thick; and when it becomes thick, it becomes stinking: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became corrupt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA:) and in like manner, said of a thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it became corrupt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bad."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAdiEN","text_ar":"خَادِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] ―         -b14-  Said of a generous man, (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He refrained"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from giving], (S, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and refused."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna fulaAnN yuEoTiY vum~a xadaEa","text_ar":"كَانَ فُلَانٌ يُعْطِى ثُمَّ خَدَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one used to give; then he refrained, and refused"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadaEahu","text_ar":"خَدَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEN","text_ar":"خَدْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severed, his"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vein called the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axodaE","text_ar":"اَخْدَع"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","Lh","K","S","Mgh","AZ","KL","L","Lth","A","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n10118","headword_ar":"خدّعهُ","root":"xdE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taxodiyEN","text_ar":"تَخْدِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, third sentence. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xud~iEa","text_ar":"خُدِّعَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was deceived, deluded, beguiled, circumvented,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outwitted, repeatedly, so that he became experienced:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was deceived,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in war, time after time, so that he became skilful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became experienced in affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became experienced in affairs, sound in judgment, cunning, and guileful."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n10127","headword_ar":"خَدْعَةٌ","root":"xdE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single act of deceit, delusion, guile, circumvention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outwitting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) It is said in a trad., (Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHarobu xadoEapN","text_ar":"الحَرْبُ خَدْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xudoEapN","text_ar":"خُدْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xidoEapN","text_ar":"خِدْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xudaEapN","text_ar":"خُدَعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, Ks, S, Mgh, K,) accord. to different relaters; (Th, Mgh, K;) the first being the most chaste, (S, Mgh, Msb,) said to be the form used by Mo- hammad; (Th, Mgh, Msb;) the second ascribed by El-Khattábee to the vulgar; (TA;) the last the best in point of meaning: (Mgh:) i. e., accord. to the first reading, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"War is"},{"kind":"text","text":"finished by"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single act of deceit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; (Mgh, O, K;) accord. to the second,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"war is a thing by which one is deceived;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"war is deceived;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for when one of the two parties deceives the other, it is as though the war itself were deceived; (IAth, TA;) [accord. to the third,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"war is a mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of deceiving;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and accord. to the fourth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"war is a deceiver of those engaged in it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Mgh, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the frequent deceits which occur therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)       -A2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slumber."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","TA","S","Msb","K","AZ","Ks","IAth"]},{"entry_id":"n10128","headword_ar":"خُدْعَةٌ","root":"xdE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing by which,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which, one deceives, deludes, beguiles, circumvents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outwits;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luEobapN","text_ar":"لُعْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ a thing with which one plays. ” (Msb.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEapN","text_ar":"خَدْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whom people deceive, delude, beguile, circumvent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outwit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luEonapN","text_ar":"لُعْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies one “ who is much cursed. ” (TA.) [See, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEapN","text_ar":"خَدْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". The comparison of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xudoEapN","text_ar":"خُدْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in one sense with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luEobapN","text_ar":"لُعْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in another sense with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luEonapN","text_ar":"لُعْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", suggests that one of the explanations above may perhaps be founded upon a mistranscription. On"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEolapN","text_ar":"فُعْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the measure of a word having the sense of a pass. part. n., see a remark of IB voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqaTN","text_ar":"لَقَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadiyEapN","text_ar":"خَدِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n10129","headword_ar":"خِدْعَةٌ","root":"xdE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of deceiving, deluding, beguiling, circumventing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"outwitting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEapN","text_ar":"خَدْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n10130","headword_ar":"خُدَعَةٌ","root":"xdE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAdiEN","text_ar":"خَادِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places: ―         -b2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xadoEapN","text_ar":"خَدْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}